allowance(address,address).details: Returns the amount of tokens approved by the owner that can be transferred to the spender's account.

params._owner: The address of the owner of the tokens.

approve(address,uint256).details: Approve the passed address to spend the specified amount of tokens on behalf of msg.sender.

params._spender: The address which will spend the funds.
params._value: The amount of tokens to be spent.

returns._0: A boolean that indicates if the operation was successful.

balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address.

params._owner: The address to query the balance of.

burn(address,uint256).details: Burn tokens from the sender's account.         check on chain doesn't use chain id, this is so contract can be adaptable to more chain burnable by pool redemption contract

params.amount: The amount of tokens to burn.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the operation succeeded.

burnFrom(address,uint256).details: Burn tokens from a specified account, subject to allowance.

params._amount: The amount of tokens to burn.
params._from: The address whose tokens will be burned.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the operation succeeded.

changeSupplyOnBsc(uint256).details: Tuins supply on bsc should only be changeable by the Tuins wallet.      restrict access using a modifier

changeSupplyOnEth(uint256).details: Tuins supply on eth should only be changeable by the Tuins wallet.      restrict access using a modifier

constructor.details: Constructor that gives poolContract initial max tokens. poolContract lists      tokens on exchanges.

decreaseApproval(address,uint256).details: Decreases the amount of tokens that an owner has allowed to a spender.

params._subtractedValue: The amount of tokens to decrease the allowance by.

returns._0: A boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded.

increaseApproval(address,uint256).details: Increases the amount of tokens that an owner has allowed to a spender.

params._addedValue: The amount of tokens to increase the allowance by.

returns._0: A boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded.

maxSupply().details: maxsupply_on_eth + maxsupplyon_bsc. this is the total amount of tokens that would ever be issued

mint(address,uint256).details: Creates new tokens and assigns them to an address in this case should be the pool contract.      check on chain doesn't use chain id, this is so contract can be adaptable to more chains mintable       by admin

params.account: The address to which the tokens will be minted.
params.amount: The amount of tokens to be minted.

returns._0: A boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded.

setOwner(address).details: function that sets the owner of the TUIN contract to _surryWallet        initially the contract owner is set to the contracts deployer address

transfer(address,uint256).details: After a user purchases TUIN, a user must be able to transfer tuin token for a specified address.          Tuin are redeemable 1:1 for profit

returns._0: A boolean that indicates if the operation was successful.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfer tokens from one address to another.

params._from: The address which you want to send tokens from.
params._to: The address which you want to transfer to.
params._value: The amount of tokens to be transferred.

returns._0: A boolean that indicates if the operation was successful
